<TITLE> Govt okays 10 more private-sector power plants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com) -- The interim advisory council granted permission to set up 10 new private-sector power plants with a capacity of 190 megawatts Monday. The government will buy power at between Tk 2.28 to Tk 2.49 per unit from the plants. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said: "The power plants will be set up in 10 locations around the country." "A similar offer was rejected earlier because of irregularities. After a fresh tender, 37 proposals came in, 10 of which were finalised. "The new power projects will save the government Tk 411 crore," he said. bdnews24.com/a
